WEBVTT

00:02.069 --> 00:04.937
It's called "eSports,"
and it's real.

00:04.939 --> 00:07.139
Professional video gamers
going head-to-head

00:07.141 --> 00:09.474
as a stadium full of people
watch.

00:09.476 --> 00:11.076
[ Crowd shouts "BoneDevil" ]
Oh, and here he comes,

00:11.078 --> 00:13.211
the defending "Voyage Quest"
champion --

00:13.213 --> 00:15.080
BoneDevil666.

00:15.082 --> 00:17.015
Let's see if we can get a word.
Mr. Devil! Mr. Devil!

00:17.017 --> 00:18.617
Can I get two words
from you?

00:18.619 --> 00:21.019
Uh, sure. Yes.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.755
A win for you today
would bring your team

00:23.757 --> 00:25.624
one step closer
to the world championships

00:25.626 --> 00:27.025
in Pyongyang.

00:27.027 --> 00:28.493
Are you feeling
the pressure?

00:28.495 --> 00:30.763
The Big Bone dominates
"Voyage Quest."

00:30.765 --> 00:32.631
That's
an undisputed fact.

00:32.633 --> 00:34.166
And anyone who gets
in his way

00:34.168 --> 00:35.768
is gonna be looking
at the business end

00:35.770 --> 00:37.902
of a Complainium
Broadsword.

00:37.904 --> 00:39.171
No more questions.
What?

00:39.173 --> 00:41.239
Hey, hey, hey.
Can I get your autograph?

00:41.241 --> 00:42.240
Oh, yeah, sure.

00:42.242 --> 00:44.108
Who should I, uh,
make it out to?

00:44.110 --> 00:45.377
[ Crowd gasps ]
Barbara: Oh, my God!

00:45.379 --> 00:49.047
BoneDevil666 has just been
ruthlessly attacked!

00:49.049 --> 00:51.583
[ Crying ]
Why? Why? Why? Why?

00:51.585 --> 00:53.585
[ Gunshot ]

00:53.587 --> 00:55.854
♪♪

00:55.856 --> 00:59.992
Atkins: BoneDevil666
is the nom de guerre

00:59.994 --> 01:03.328
of 22-year-old
professional gamer Paul Boneson.

01:03.330 --> 01:04.529
[ Horn honking ]

01:04.531 --> 01:06.398
Sorry, Murphy.
Above your pay grade.

01:06.400 --> 01:08.400
Come on, Hoffman!

01:08.402 --> 01:10.803
[ Curtain slides ]

01:10.805 --> 01:13.005
Boneson plays a game called
"Voyage Quest"

01:13.007 --> 01:15.207
for a professional gaming team
known as SharkSpark.

01:15.209 --> 01:17.075
The attack,
which you're seeing now,

01:17.077 --> 01:18.477
has taken his fingers
out of the running

01:18.479 --> 01:19.611
for the world championships.

01:19.613 --> 01:21.613
Sir, I thought
we were taking cases

01:21.615 --> 01:23.548
outside of
law enforcement,

01:23.550 --> 01:27.085
like international espionage
and haunted trains?

01:27.087 --> 01:28.620
Damn it, Mom.
Your unique brand of skepticism

01:28.622 --> 01:30.222
is gonna tear
this team apart!

01:30.224 --> 01:33.358
Fortunately, I anticipated
Tribeca's rock-hard cynicism.

01:33.360 --> 01:35.227
Therefore, this briefing
will be given

01:35.229 --> 01:38.030
by the director of the Special
Division Force himself...

01:38.032 --> 01:40.833
[ Brakes squeak ]
...Vice President Joe Perry.

01:40.835 --> 01:42.501
[ Door opens ]

01:42.503 --> 01:45.170
♪♪

01:45.172 --> 01:47.239
BoneDevil666
is the nom de guerre

01:47.241 --> 01:48.773
of a 22-year-old gamer
named Paul --

01:48.775 --> 01:50.042
Sorry, Joe.
I-I covered that.

01:50.044 --> 01:51.776
You were further down the road
than I thought.

01:51.778 --> 01:53.712
Did Tribeca show her
unique brand of skepticism?

01:53.714 --> 01:54.979
That's exactly
where we are.

01:54.981 --> 01:56.915
The video gaming
industry

01:56.917 --> 01:58.517
brings more money
into the U.S. economy

01:58.519 --> 02:01.186
than missiles, oil,
and coffee-cup sleeves combined.

02:01.188 --> 02:04.589
If a foreign entity wants
to disrupt that industry,

02:04.591 --> 02:05.724
we wanna know about it,

02:05.726 --> 02:07.659
and ideally,
we wanna stop it.

02:07.661 --> 02:09.794
You know what I just
heard you say?

02:09.796 --> 02:11.996
"I'm sending you to prison
for 20 years."

02:11.998 --> 02:13.666
Oh, my God.
Are you still on that?

02:13.668 --> 02:15.333
It's been like 20 years.

02:15.335 --> 02:17.135
You locked me up
and threw away the key!

02:17.137 --> 02:19.271
I didn't know
that was the only copy!

02:20.274 --> 02:22.607
Look, Tribeca,
that was a different time.

02:22.609 --> 02:24.877
Back then, putting people
in jail was all the rage,

02:24.879 --> 02:27.345
and I guess I just jumped
on the bandwagon.

02:27.347 --> 02:29.414
All I care about is
the safety of this nation.

02:29.416 --> 02:31.216
That's why I brought you
on board,

02:31.218 --> 02:33.886
because I knew
I could count on you.

02:33.888 --> 02:36.421
So, can I...
count on you...

02:36.423 --> 02:39.424
to care...about the safety...
of our nation?

02:39.426 --> 02:42.827
♪♪

02:42.829 --> 02:44.362
Yes, sir.

02:44.364 --> 02:45.898
All right, then.

02:45.900 --> 02:48.767
BoneDevil666 is recovering
in a hospital bed

02:48.769 --> 02:50.435
in Little Rock,
Arkansas.

02:50.437 --> 02:52.771
It's the gaming capital
of the United States.

02:52.773 --> 02:54.239
Find out who attacked him
and why.

02:54.241 --> 02:56.241
And even though
everything you're doing

02:56.243 --> 02:58.843
will be perfectly legal,
don't tell anyone anything,

02:58.845 --> 03:00.579
unless you follow up with,
"Just kidding."

03:00.581 --> 03:05.650
♪♪

03:05.652 --> 03:07.852
[ Monitor beeping ]
[ Indistinct talking over P.A. ]

03:07.854 --> 03:09.254
[ Groans ]

03:09.256 --> 03:11.323
So, you didn't get a look
at the guy who attacked you?

03:11.325 --> 03:13.926
I just remember
he was wearing a ski mask.

03:13.928 --> 03:16.128
Lose the attitude,
you little prick.

03:16.130 --> 03:17.930
Now, it's gonna
be painful,

03:17.932 --> 03:19.531
but I wanna get
your fingers moving.

03:19.533 --> 03:21.666
[ Scoffs ]

03:21.668 --> 03:24.937
♪♪

03:24.939 --> 03:27.606
[ Groans ]
I can't do it.

03:27.608 --> 03:30.008
Who are these people?
What are they doing here?

03:30.010 --> 03:31.209
We're trying to get
to the bottom

03:31.211 --> 03:32.677
of who attacked
Mr. Boneson.

03:32.679 --> 03:34.813
A better question might be,
"Who are you?"

03:34.815 --> 03:36.548
And an even better question
might be,

03:36.550 --> 03:39.151
"If prostitution is the oldest
profession in the world,

03:39.153 --> 03:41.686
who earned the money to pay
for the first prostitute?"

03:41.688 --> 03:44.222
I'm Becky Bunnker,
and it's obvious what happened.

03:44.224 --> 03:47.960
Someone, who probably doesn't
stand for the national anthem,

03:47.962 --> 03:49.828
didn't want him
to become world champion.

03:49.830 --> 03:52.230
Yeah, well, it doesn't seem
like Mr. Jelly Fingers over here

03:52.232 --> 03:54.232
even cares about
the world championships.

03:54.234 --> 03:57.169
You couldn't be more wrong.
"Voyage Quest" is his life.

03:57.171 --> 03:59.171
I don't know who told you
otherwise.

03:59.173 --> 04:01.906
Actually, Beck, I'm just done
with this whole thing.

04:01.908 --> 04:03.508
I think
I'm just gonna get a job

04:03.510 --> 04:05.377
teaching animals
to play video games.

04:05.379 --> 04:06.979
You don't know what
you're saying, BoneDevil.

04:06.981 --> 04:08.380
We had plans, right?

04:08.382 --> 04:10.048
We were gonna buy
that Fuddruckers

04:10.050 --> 04:12.451
with your winnings.
[ Cellphone rings ]

04:12.453 --> 04:15.187
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Tribeca.

04:15.189 --> 04:16.855
Right away, sir.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:16.857 --> 04:18.190
This just in --

04:18.192 --> 04:20.325
the attacker turned himself in
to Little Rock PD.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.726
He's at the station now.

04:21.728 --> 04:23.128
Well, don't you think
we should have a word with him

04:23.130 --> 04:24.663
before somebody else does?

04:24.665 --> 04:30.535
♪♪

04:30.537 --> 04:33.271
How much longer
do I have to wait here?

04:33.273 --> 04:35.407
I'm trying to confess
to a crime!

04:35.409 --> 04:37.409
Take a number.

04:37.411 --> 04:40.612
-Yo, pastrami, please.
-Coming up.

04:40.614 --> 04:42.614
[ Police radio chatter ]

04:42.616 --> 04:45.617
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:45.619 --> 04:47.219
[ Engine starts ]

04:47.221 --> 04:55.627
♪♪

04:55.629 --> 04:57.229
[ Chuckles ]

05:00.968 --> 05:02.768
[ Grunts ] I want answers.

05:02.770 --> 05:04.836
And I want 'em now!

05:04.838 --> 05:06.939
[ Grunting ]

05:14.848 --> 05:16.714
[ Slurps ]

05:16.716 --> 05:17.583
[ Sighs ]

05:17.585 --> 05:18.984
Just do it.

05:18.986 --> 05:20.185
Just get it over with.

05:20.187 --> 05:21.987
We just wanna know
what happened.

05:21.989 --> 05:23.655
They're gonna come
after me, man.

05:23.657 --> 05:26.392
They're gonna kill you because
of what you did to Paul Boneson?

05:26.394 --> 05:27.459
Yes!

05:27.461 --> 05:28.994
[ Whispers ]
To keep me quiet!

05:28.996 --> 05:29.995
Do you know them?

05:29.997 --> 05:31.463
[ Normal voice ]
It's my team.

05:31.465 --> 05:33.599
It's SharkSpark.
They're me. I'm them.

05:33.601 --> 05:36.802
Why would SharkSpark wanna go
after its own players?

05:36.804 --> 05:40.205
It's all about coins, man.
All they want is coins.

05:40.207 --> 05:42.540
"They"?
The company?

05:42.542 --> 05:44.676
It's the company working
with the gamers,

05:44.678 --> 05:47.345
working with the Mafia,
working with the CIA,

05:47.347 --> 05:50.215
working with a temp agency.

05:50.217 --> 05:52.017
This is a riddle
wrapped in a sudoku

05:52.019 --> 05:54.352
tied up with a crossword
suspended over the jumble.

05:54.354 --> 05:57.823
And they're gonna come after me.
I'm a dead man.

05:57.825 --> 05:59.958
Look, we're gonna
keep you safe.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.559
You can't keep me safe
from them.

06:01.561 --> 06:03.895
We're supposed to try.

06:03.897 --> 06:08.366
♪♪

06:08.368 --> 06:09.435
Why don't we take him
to a motel,

06:09.437 --> 06:11.303
sit with him till
he calms down?

06:11.305 --> 06:12.570
You sure?

06:12.572 --> 06:14.506
W-We don't even really know
what's going on.

06:14.508 --> 06:17.575
Well, you said it yourself,
it's a stupid case.

06:17.577 --> 06:20.578
♪♪

06:20.580 --> 06:23.181
You have nothing
to worry about.

06:23.183 --> 06:25.651
I won't let you out
of my sight.

06:25.653 --> 06:27.853
♪♪

06:27.855 --> 06:29.521
I'm gonna run in for some beer
real quick.

06:29.523 --> 06:30.989
You want anything?

06:30.991 --> 06:32.057
Could you please hurry?!

06:32.059 --> 06:34.059
Yeah, totally.
I'll be right back.

06:34.061 --> 06:38.063
[ Mid-tempo music
plays on radio ]

06:38.065 --> 06:40.466
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:40.468 --> 06:46.805
♪♪

06:46.807 --> 06:48.874
[ Screams ]

06:48.876 --> 06:50.275
Should I get
this ski mask?

06:50.277 --> 06:52.210
[ Panting ]
Ah, you know what?

06:52.212 --> 06:54.813
I'm never gonna use this.

06:54.815 --> 06:57.816
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:57.818 --> 07:02.154
♪♪

07:02.156 --> 07:03.555
[ Screams ]

07:03.557 --> 07:05.824
Crazy sale on knives, dude!
You want one?!

07:05.826 --> 07:06.758
Aaah!

07:06.760 --> 07:08.494
I'm getting you one.

07:08.496 --> 07:10.896
[ Panting ]

07:10.898 --> 07:13.365
♪♪

07:13.367 --> 07:15.100
[ Whirring ]

07:15.102 --> 07:16.368
[ Screams ]

07:16.370 --> 07:18.904
Yo! They're doing
free tank rides!

07:18.906 --> 07:20.839
You gotta try it!
Aaaah!

07:20.841 --> 07:22.240
Shit. Right.
The beer.

07:22.242 --> 07:26.178
[ Panting ]

07:26.180 --> 07:27.846
[ Knock on window ]

07:27.848 --> 07:30.182
[ Sighing ] Oh.

07:30.184 --> 07:31.850
Finally.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.352
Can we get out of here?

07:35.523 --> 07:39.457
♪♪

07:39.459 --> 07:40.726
All right!

07:40.728 --> 07:42.660
[ Groans ]

07:42.662 --> 07:44.129
Here we go!

07:44.131 --> 07:47.665
♪♪

07:47.667 --> 07:49.067
[ Sighs ]

07:49.069 --> 07:52.470
Ah, no need, dude.
Beer's on me.

07:52.472 --> 07:53.939
[ Chuckles ]

07:56.009 --> 07:58.744
You're a Fudgsicle.

07:58.746 --> 08:01.547
You're a Creamsicle.
You're a Bomb Pop.

08:01.549 --> 08:03.815
You're lactose intolerant.
[ Children screaming ]

08:03.817 --> 08:06.218
Hey! Hey!

08:06.220 --> 08:10.322
A man died here!
Have a little respect!

08:14.028 --> 08:15.661
I want answers!

08:18.032 --> 08:19.465
I found something.

08:20.367 --> 08:21.767
What the hell is that?

08:21.769 --> 08:23.368
It's like a dollar,
but not.

08:23.370 --> 08:24.903
No, no, no.
It's got too many colors.

08:24.905 --> 08:26.104
It's a Euro.

08:26.106 --> 08:28.306
Maybe fake money
from a board game?

08:28.308 --> 08:30.442
Look at this seam of silver
going through it.

08:30.444 --> 08:33.511
It's a Euro.
It's money they use in Europe.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.581
Whatever it is,
it scares the hell out of me.

08:35.583 --> 08:37.649
I can slip this to a contact
I have at the Mint,

08:37.651 --> 08:40.385
off the record.
So, we have a kid carrying

08:40.387 --> 08:42.988
some kind of spooky money
in his pocket...

08:42.990 --> 08:44.322
[ Sternly ]
A Euro.

08:44.324 --> 08:46.992
Someone needs to go undercover
with this...

08:46.994 --> 08:48.726
SharkSpark Gaming team.

08:48.728 --> 08:49.861
I'll do it.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.797
Mom, you've never played
a video game in your life.

08:51.799 --> 08:53.865
I played Simon.
That's not a video game!

08:53.867 --> 08:56.201
It had a battery.
No, it needs to be me.

08:56.203 --> 08:57.535
Right, the one good thing

08:57.537 --> 08:59.204
about being abandoned
at the age of two

08:59.206 --> 09:01.006
is that every foster home
I was placed in

09:01.008 --> 09:02.874
had a different
video game system.

09:02.876 --> 09:04.209
A.J.'s our man.

09:04.211 --> 09:06.478
No. No, no, no.
It's too dangerous.

09:06.480 --> 09:07.813
I must've missed the meeting
where you decide

09:07.815 --> 09:09.615
which missions I go on
and which I don't!

09:09.617 --> 09:11.617
It was on the calendar.
I am not saying this
as your mother.

09:11.619 --> 09:14.620
I am saying this as somebody
who has 30 years of experience!

09:14.622 --> 09:16.688
20 of which were behind bars,
so -- Aah!

09:16.690 --> 09:18.290
You listen to me,
you little punk --

09:18.292 --> 09:20.892
Hey! Break it up!
<i> You</i> stay out of this!

09:20.894 --> 09:23.762
Hey!
Hands off the big man!

09:23.764 --> 09:26.765
Everybody's picking on Tribeca,
and I don't like it!

09:26.767 --> 09:28.233
Break it up!

09:28.235 --> 09:29.968
Where's A.J.?

09:29.970 --> 09:34.572
♪♪

09:34.574 --> 09:35.774
What do you want,
idiot?

09:35.776 --> 09:37.443
Heard you're down
a couple gamers.

09:37.445 --> 09:39.244
Thanks,
Google News Alert.

09:39.246 --> 09:40.646
What else you got for me?

09:40.648 --> 09:43.515
Well, just so happens
I'm looking for a new team.

09:43.517 --> 09:45.984
Sorry, new phone.
Who dis?

09:45.986 --> 09:48.586
Look, we both know gold coins
are where it's at, bro.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.922
Just so happens,
I just took second place

09:50.924 --> 09:53.191
at the Slovenian
"Voyage Quest" Championships

09:53.193 --> 09:55.060
with over 10 million
gold coins.

09:55.062 --> 09:57.595
Slovenia?
That's hardcore.

09:57.597 --> 10:01.199
BaguetteBardot1-800-555-1212
won that, didn't she?

10:01.201 --> 10:03.335
You don't beat
BaguetteBardot.

10:03.337 --> 10:06.604
Not on her worst day.
Come on in.

10:06.606 --> 10:10.809
♪♪

10:10.811 --> 10:12.277
[ Video game sound effects
playing ]

10:12.279 --> 10:15.213
Have a seat,
grab a headset.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.948
You can show us
what you got.

10:16.950 --> 10:18.884
♪♪

10:18.886 --> 10:20.352
Oh.

10:21.889 --> 10:24.289
You want a little something
to get your engine running

10:24.291 --> 10:26.091
before I check you out?

10:26.093 --> 10:27.292
Uh...

10:27.294 --> 10:29.695
I don't recognize
that brand.

10:29.697 --> 10:32.698
That's 'cause it's illegal,
bitch.

10:32.700 --> 10:35.501
It's strawberry lemonade mixed
with horse adrenalin.

10:35.503 --> 10:36.702
They used to give it
to the NASA monkeys

10:36.704 --> 10:38.370
to keep them awake
in space.

10:38.372 --> 10:40.105
Well, sure,
I'll try it.

10:40.107 --> 10:42.508
[ Chuckles ]

10:42.510 --> 10:43.742
[ Grunts ]

10:45.913 --> 10:54.252
♪♪

10:54.254 --> 10:55.721
Whoo!

10:55.723 --> 11:01.126
♪♪

11:01.128 --> 11:03.261
[ Distorted voices ]

11:03.263 --> 11:05.197
[ Chuckles ]

11:05.199 --> 11:07.733
♪♪

11:07.735 --> 11:10.135
Okay, so, all you gotta do
is craft a spear,

11:10.137 --> 11:13.138
kill a Lesser Nerblet,
and raid his hut for the coins.

11:13.140 --> 11:14.940
That sounds easy!

11:14.942 --> 11:17.609
Yeah. Right.

11:17.611 --> 11:18.944
Huh? Huh?

11:18.946 --> 11:20.145
Now do it.

11:20.147 --> 11:22.181
Well, why stop there?

11:23.817 --> 11:25.884
Tie my hands.

11:25.886 --> 11:28.153
♪♪

11:28.155 --> 11:30.622
And...go.

11:30.624 --> 11:33.091
[<i> Chiming</i> ]

11:33.093 --> 11:35.160
<i> My hut! My coins!</i>

11:35.162 --> 11:37.695
♪♪

11:37.697 --> 11:38.496
Done!

11:38.498 --> 11:40.966
You can have
Ozzy's room.

11:40.968 --> 11:43.168
[ Sighs ]

11:45.239 --> 11:47.039
Whoo.

11:47.041 --> 11:51.210
♪♪

11:54.748 --> 11:56.548
[ Sighs ]

11:56.550 --> 11:58.283
We haven't seen Ozzy
for a couple days,

11:58.285 --> 11:59.885
so I guess all this stuff
is yours now.

11:59.887 --> 12:01.353
Hey, man,
is that the bathroom?

12:01.355 --> 12:02.954
'Cause this horse adrenaline
is going right through me.

12:02.956 --> 12:04.289
Yeah, don't freak out

12:04.291 --> 12:06.758
if you fill up
the whole bowl, okay?

12:06.760 --> 12:08.360
Welcome
to SharkSpark.

12:08.362 --> 12:09.928
[ Chuckles ]

12:12.032 --> 12:14.432
[ Water running ]

12:14.434 --> 12:15.633
Hello?

12:15.635 --> 12:19.171
♪♪

12:19.173 --> 12:20.906
You got a bad washer
in here.

12:20.908 --> 12:22.107
I should have one
in my truck.

12:22.109 --> 12:23.609
Okay. Thanks.

12:25.713 --> 12:29.047
♪♪

12:29.049 --> 12:31.850
So, you're the new number one
around here?

12:31.852 --> 12:33.251
Looks that way.
Hmm.

12:33.253 --> 12:36.522
Being number one comes
with certain...perks.

12:36.524 --> 12:37.723
And what are those?

12:37.725 --> 12:39.191
Full medical, dental,

12:39.193 --> 12:40.658
and optical coverage,

12:40.660 --> 12:43.461
including one pair
of free glasses per year.

12:43.463 --> 12:45.797
Ooh.
Designer brands included?

12:45.799 --> 12:47.065
Oh, yes.

12:47.067 --> 12:49.467
Sounds like I'm gonna be
well taken care of.

12:49.469 --> 12:50.936
Oh, I almost forgot.

12:50.938 --> 12:53.205
You get
a free team shirt.

12:54.875 --> 12:56.408
Do I get the team bra?

12:56.410 --> 12:59.144
Let's see how good of a player
you are.

12:59.146 --> 13:01.880
♪♪

13:01.882 --> 13:03.148
Becky: Oh, my God.

13:03.150 --> 13:04.816
Oh, my God!

13:04.818 --> 13:06.484
You're amazing!

13:06.486 --> 13:08.086
You wanna give it
a shot?

13:08.088 --> 13:09.687
No, I don't understand
these games.

13:09.689 --> 13:10.956
I just like to watch.

13:10.958 --> 13:12.424
Ooh, grab the coins.
Grab the coins!

13:12.426 --> 13:13.825
What is it with you people
and the coins?

13:13.827 --> 13:17.829
That's not how you win!
God, this mattress sucks!

13:17.831 --> 13:18.964
This...

13:22.702 --> 13:24.570
What the hell?

13:24.572 --> 13:25.637
[ Grunts ]
Aah!

13:25.639 --> 13:27.906
[ Body thuds ]

13:27.908 --> 13:29.775
Ah!

13:29.777 --> 13:30.909
[ Breathing heavily ]

13:30.911 --> 13:32.310
Please don't kill me!

13:32.312 --> 13:33.979
What is it with you people
and getting killed?!

13:33.981 --> 13:36.314
He's crazy!
He'll stop at nothing!

13:36.316 --> 13:38.049
Who?
You don't understand.

13:38.051 --> 13:39.251
This is
so much bigger than --

13:39.253 --> 13:40.586
No, no, no!
Wait, wait, wait.

13:40.588 --> 13:42.720
Don't start that.
Just let me think.

13:42.722 --> 13:45.257
Gold coins.
Everybody wants gold coins.

13:45.259 --> 13:49.795
And this kid somehow's got
piles of fake money.

13:49.797 --> 13:51.329
I-It's gotta be
connected!

13:51.331 --> 13:52.397
It is connected!
I can tell you --

13:52.399 --> 13:53.665
Would you shut up
for a second?

13:53.667 --> 13:56.001
I'm trying to piece this thing
together.

13:56.003 --> 13:58.604
What if it isn't
fake money?

13:58.606 --> 14:01.139
Wait, what if it's real money
and the coins are --

14:01.141 --> 14:02.407
He's laundering money
through the ga--

14:02.409 --> 14:05.543
Can you just be quiet
for five seconds?!

14:05.545 --> 14:07.879
Okay, so, you got
fake money going in,

14:07.881 --> 14:09.080
real money coming back.

14:09.082 --> 14:11.483
Ooh! It's laundering!
Of course!

14:11.485 --> 14:14.152
BoneDevil, he -- he doesn't want
to collect coins,

14:14.154 --> 14:16.354
so he's useless,
so Ozzy takes him out,

14:16.356 --> 14:18.490
but Ozzy's got a big mouth,
so they take Ozzy out.

14:18.492 --> 14:21.159
Ozzy's dead?!
Can you just shush?!

14:21.161 --> 14:22.760
You need to protect me!

14:22.762 --> 14:24.430
'Cause if he thinks I talked,
he's --

14:24.432 --> 14:27.032
Look, I am definitely good
at protecting people.

14:27.034 --> 14:28.900
You don't need to worry
about that.

14:28.902 --> 14:31.970
But I need to meet this big guy
who's running everything.

14:31.972 --> 14:33.305
Absolutely not!
No way!

14:33.307 --> 14:36.108
Come on!
There's no way I can finish it.

14:36.110 --> 14:39.377
It's an international
money-laundering scheme.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.313
The money changes hands
through the gold coins

14:41.315 --> 14:42.780
in "Voyage Quest."

14:42.782 --> 14:45.317
Oh, and those weird
paper rectangles we found,

14:45.319 --> 14:47.519
they're called Euros.

14:47.521 --> 14:49.254
This is from my buddy
at the Mint.

14:49.256 --> 14:50.856
They're called Euros.

14:50.858 --> 14:52.324
[ Glass shatters ]

14:52.326 --> 14:54.125
Oh, and Becky,
who was BoneDevil's girlfriend,

14:54.127 --> 14:55.861
but is now my girlfriend --
I'll get to that in a second --

14:55.863 --> 14:57.529
she's gonna arrange a meet-up
with the head

14:57.531 --> 14:59.264
of the whole operation.
Tribeca: That's great.

14:59.266 --> 15:00.666
We'll go in as a team,
fully armed --

15:00.668 --> 15:03.201
No, no, no, no.
It has to be only me.

15:03.203 --> 15:04.602
No, we --

15:04.604 --> 15:07.339
All right,
just don't let your guard down

15:07.341 --> 15:09.741
because some floozy let you
jiggle her love button.

15:09.743 --> 15:11.943
You can't push someone else's
button in this game.

15:11.945 --> 15:13.145
You can in Simon.

15:13.147 --> 15:14.780
All right, everybody.
Just stop.

15:16.550 --> 15:18.484
All right, A.J.
It's all you.

15:18.486 --> 15:19.685
Yeah!

15:19.687 --> 15:23.088
♪♪

15:25.926 --> 15:29.461
♪♪

15:29.463 --> 15:32.330
[ French accent ]
Come in, come in.

15:32.332 --> 15:36.067
Pay no attention to...
the rainbow!

15:36.069 --> 15:37.202
[ Sighs ]

15:37.204 --> 15:40.405
So beautiful,
don't you think?

15:40.407 --> 15:43.942
Fireball!

15:43.944 --> 15:46.678
<i> Bienvenue,</i> welcome.

15:46.680 --> 15:50.816
My name...
is Pierre Cardin.

15:50.818 --> 15:53.752
And I hear that you are
the new Chef des Jeux Vidéos.

15:53.754 --> 15:55.087
Uh, uh, yeah, I guess.

15:55.089 --> 15:56.754
I mean, some people think
I'm pretty good.

15:56.756 --> 15:58.490
[ Laughs ]

15:58.492 --> 15:59.891
"Pretty good"?

15:59.893 --> 16:01.559
Pretty good, mon Dieu!

16:01.561 --> 16:03.629
But you delight me
with your modesty.

16:03.631 --> 16:05.764
He's actually one of the best
I've ever seen.

16:05.766 --> 16:07.365
Hmm.

16:07.367 --> 16:10.702
You know, people love to throw
around this word "best" --

16:10.704 --> 16:12.237
Best Buy,

16:12.239 --> 16:14.039
Seattle's Best Coffee,

16:14.041 --> 16:16.308
This Country's Best Yogurt.

16:16.310 --> 16:18.043
But these are
just words, no?

16:18.045 --> 16:20.378
Would you be willing
to, say...

16:20.380 --> 16:24.383
stake your life on the fact
that you are the best?

16:26.320 --> 16:27.853
I-I'm not sure I follow.

16:27.855 --> 16:30.255
This is the latest
in VR gaming.

16:30.257 --> 16:33.191
You will be completely,
totally immersed

16:33.193 --> 16:36.528
in the virtual landscape
of "Voyage Quest."

16:36.530 --> 16:38.997
You will not only see and hear
everything around you,

16:38.999 --> 16:44.470
but this is also what we call
total biological simulation,

16:44.472 --> 16:46.204
or total BS.

16:46.206 --> 16:48.140
Wouldn't that be TBS?
[ Chuckles ]

16:48.142 --> 16:50.008
Very funny.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.677
What I mean to say is,

16:51.679 --> 16:56.482
that this game will connect
to your central nervous system.

16:56.484 --> 16:59.617
Whatever the avatar experiences
in the game,

16:59.619 --> 17:03.155
the game player will experience,
as well.

17:03.157 --> 17:08.960
If, for example,
your avatar were to...die,

17:08.962 --> 17:12.630
the human controller will die,
as well.

17:12.632 --> 17:15.100
♪♪

17:15.102 --> 17:16.634
[ Coughs ] Mom?

17:16.636 --> 17:19.338
Jesus Christ.
A.J., get out of there!

17:21.175 --> 17:23.241
All right.

17:23.243 --> 17:24.710
Let's give this a whirl.

17:24.712 --> 17:26.578
Now, how -- how exactly
do you make this --

17:26.580 --> 17:28.514
[ Whirring ]
Aah! [ Groans ]

17:28.516 --> 17:32.117
The game is now connected
to your spinal cord.

17:32.119 --> 17:34.052
How -- Oh.

17:34.054 --> 17:35.320
Okay.

17:35.322 --> 17:37.455
Uh...
[<i> Beeping</i> ]

17:37.457 --> 17:40.926
Okay, so, you got tennis,
Ping-Pong...

17:40.928 --> 17:42.928
Keep scrolling down.

17:42.930 --> 17:44.730
"Voyage Quest."

17:44.732 --> 17:47.665
Now hit the virtual
"start" button.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.067
Uh, okay.

17:49.069 --> 17:50.536
[<i> Fanfare</i> ]

17:50.538 --> 17:51.737
I'm in!

17:51.739 --> 17:54.672
Wow!

17:54.674 --> 17:56.875
It's so real.

17:56.877 --> 17:58.810
I-I-I can -- I can feel
the breeze through my --

17:58.812 --> 18:01.613
[ Thuds ]
Aah! Ow!

18:01.615 --> 18:03.949
♪♪

18:03.951 --> 18:06.418
Becky,
what the hell?!

18:06.420 --> 18:13.425
♪♪

18:13.427 --> 18:20.165
♪♪

18:20.167 --> 18:24.035
BaguetteBardot?
The world's best gamer.

18:24.037 --> 18:25.637
[ French accent ]
<i> Enchanté.</i>

18:25.639 --> 18:27.839
Cardin: Obviously, the only way
for me to actually know

18:27.841 --> 18:32.310
if you are the best
is for you to play my champion.

18:32.312 --> 18:35.513
So, the rules will
be as follows --

18:35.515 --> 18:41.186
If Baguette wins,
well...you die.

18:41.188 --> 18:45.657
But if you win,
I will allow you to arrest me

18:45.659 --> 18:49.194
for money laundering
and international espionage,

18:49.196 --> 18:52.197
Angela Geils Jr.

18:52.199 --> 18:53.732
[ Gasps ]

18:53.734 --> 18:55.333
He's made. He's made!

18:55.335 --> 18:56.734
I don't like this!

18:56.736 --> 18:58.804
We wasted an entire
half-sandwich!

18:58.806 --> 19:00.205
Scholls, you have to hack
into the game!

19:00.207 --> 19:01.607
You have to get him
out of there!

19:01.609 --> 19:05.343
♪♪

19:05.345 --> 19:07.545
It's...

19:07.547 --> 19:09.747
beautiful.

19:09.749 --> 19:11.083
♪♪

19:11.085 --> 19:13.351
[ Whirring ]

19:13.353 --> 19:16.221
[<i> Beeping</i> ]

19:16.223 --> 19:21.159
♪♪

19:21.161 --> 19:23.028
Space Needle!

19:23.030 --> 19:25.230
Troll Blanket!

19:25.232 --> 19:26.832
Cornish Game Hen.

19:26.834 --> 19:28.233
Leg of Lamb!

19:28.235 --> 19:30.168
Grease Pencil!
[ Grunts ]

19:30.170 --> 19:32.370
[ Groans ]

19:32.372 --> 19:34.572
Banana Peel!
[ Grunts ]

19:34.574 --> 19:35.907
Ice Mushroom!

19:35.909 --> 19:36.842
Vapor Shield!

19:36.844 --> 19:37.843
Fire Rain!

19:37.845 --> 19:39.377
Globe of Conservation!

19:39.379 --> 19:40.979
Horn of Plenty!

19:40.981 --> 19:42.113
[ Horn sounds ]

19:42.115 --> 19:43.315
Technicolor Dreamcoat!

19:43.317 --> 19:44.716
Aah!
Elf Leg!

19:44.718 --> 19:45.917
Aaaah!

19:45.919 --> 19:48.053
Elf Leg!
No!

19:48.055 --> 19:50.922
Elf Leg!
Noooooo!

19:50.924 --> 19:53.459
Dagger of Espadrille!

19:53.461 --> 19:56.328
<i> Au revoir,</i>
Monsieur Geils!

19:56.330 --> 19:57.929
<i> Au revoir!</i>

19:57.931 --> 19:59.064
Nooooo!

19:59.066 --> 20:00.332
[ Groans ]

20:00.334 --> 20:03.869
Simon says...
"You're dead."

20:03.871 --> 20:07.939
♪♪

20:07.941 --> 20:09.541
No.

20:09.543 --> 20:15.881
♪♪

20:15.883 --> 20:17.415
You son of a...

20:17.417 --> 20:24.022
♪♪

20:24.024 --> 20:25.357
[ Beep ]
Cardin's in the wind.

20:25.359 --> 20:26.824
Cardin's in the wind!

20:26.826 --> 20:29.161
Don't sweat it.
We'll pick you up in 20.

20:29.163 --> 20:30.496
Cardin will get his.

20:30.498 --> 20:32.297
[ Beep ]
Roger that.

20:32.299 --> 20:39.905
♪♪

20:39.907 --> 20:41.507
[ Whirring ]

20:41.509 --> 20:43.041
[ Sighs ]

20:43.043 --> 20:45.177
[<i> Beeps</i> ]

20:45.179 --> 20:46.311
[ Whirring ]

20:46.313 --> 20:47.979
Ooh.

20:47.981 --> 20:49.647
[ Chuckles ]

20:49.649 --> 20:53.686
This feels like
a real Hula-Hoop!

20:57.525 --> 21:04.730
♪♪

